article.headline: Texas A&amp,M-CC 50, Texas-San Antonio 49
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Terence Jones drained a go-ahead 3-pointer with 1:11 remaining, and Texas A&M-Corpus Christi held on for a 50-49 victory against UTSA on Wednesday night. Jones, who led the Islanders (2-13, 1-2 Southland Conference) with 12 points, made the score 50-48 with his basket from behind the arc. Jeromie Hill cut the margin to a point by making one of two free throws with 56 seconds left, and the Roadrunners (9-7, 2-1) had the last shot, but Melvin Johnson III could not connect on a 3-point attempt. Hill and Stephen Franklin scored 10 points each for UTSA, which shot just 27.3 percent (18 for 66) from the floor, including 3 for 22 from 3-point range. Franklin had 10 rebounds. Chris Hawkins-Mast had 10 points and Myron Dempsey added eight points and 11 rebounds for Texas A&M-Corpus Christi, which ended an 11-game losing streak.
